EVENT_NARRATIVE: Multiple accidents occurred during the morning commuting period along Interstate 565 between Decatur and Huntsville in Limestone and Madison Counties.  Patchy black ice developed, especially on bridges and overpasses.
EPISODE_NARRATIVE: Patchy black ice developed, especially on bridges and overpasses, during the early morning hours.  This resulted in very slippery conditions in some areas during the morning commute. Multiple accidents occurred on Interstate 565 in Limestone into Madison Counties between Decatur and Huntsville.

EVENT_NARRATIVE: Rain changed to wet snow above 1000 FT AGL, mainly atop the higher elevations and mountains of eastern Madison County, including Monte Sano and Keel Mountain. Snowfall of 0.5 inches or less were reported, mainly on grassy or elevated surfaces.
EPISODE_NARRATIVE: A powerful upper level low pressure system moved northeast through southern Alabama into central Georgia during the morning hours of the 12th.  Widespread rainfall changed to wet snow for a brief period, mainly in the higher elevations above 1000 ft AGL elevation. This resulted in minor snow accumulations under one inch, mainly in grassy areas, of Jackson, DeKalb, Marshall and eastern Madison Counties.
